-- East Libya Security Chief Assassinated by Gunmen, LNA Says
-- B y   S a l e h   S a r r a r
-- 2012-11-21T12:51:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-21/east-libya-security-chief-assassinated-by-gunmen-lna-says.html
Armed assailants shot dead the
security chief of the eastern Libyan city of Benghazi, the Libya
 News Agency  reported.  Three armed men in a vehicle opened fire on Colonel Faraj
Dersi last night and fled the scene, Seraj Sheik, a senior
official at the local security directorate, told the Tripoli-
based news agency. Faraj died before arriving at hospital, the
agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saleh Sarar in Dubai at 
 ssarar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
